  • Method Details

    • asString

      public AsString asString(Operand<? extends TType> input, AsString.Options... options)
      Converts each entry in the given tensor to strings. Supports many numeric types and boolean.

      For Unicode, see the [https://www.tensorflow.org/tutorials/representation/unicode](Working with Unicode text) tutorial.

      Examples:

      tf.strings.as_string([3, 2]) <tf.Tensor: shape=(2,), dtype=string, numpy=array([b'3', b'2'], dtype=object)> tf.strings.as_string([3.1415926, 2.71828], precision=2).numpy() array([b'3.14', b'2.72'], dtype=object)

      Parameters:
      input - The input value
      options - carries optional attribute values
      Returns:
      a new instance of AsString

    • complex

      public <U extends TType, T extends TNumber> Complex<U> complex(Operand<T> real, Operand<T> imag, Class<U> Tout)
      Converts two real numbers to a complex number. Given a tensor real representing the real part of a complex number, and a tensor imag representing the imaginary part of a complex number, this operation returns complex numbers elementwise of the form \(a + bj\), where a represents the real part and b represents the imag part.

      The input tensors real and imag must have the same shape.

      For example: 

       # tensor 'real' is [2.25, 3.25]
 # tensor `imag` is [4.75, 5.75]
 tf.complex(real, imag) ==> [[2.25 + 4.75j], [3.25 + 5.75j]]
      Type Parameters:
      U - data type for Complex output and operands
      T - data type for Complex output and operands
      Parameters:
      real - The real value
      imag - The imag value
      Tout - The value of the Tout attribute
      Returns:
      a new instance of Complex

    • toBool

      public ToBool toBool(Operand<? extends TType> input)
      Converts a tensor to a scalar predicate. Converts a tensor to a scalar predicate with the following rules:

      • For 0D tensors, truthiness is determined by comparing against a "zero" value. For numerical types it is the obvious zero. For strings it is the empty string.

      • For >0D tensors, truthiness is determined by looking at the number of elements. If has zero elements, then the result is false. Otherwise the result is true.

      This matches the behavior of If and While for determining if a tensor counts as true/false for a branch condition.

      Parameters:
      input - The input value
      Returns:
      a new instance of ToBool
